com.qtplaf.library.database.rdbms.sql

Class Insert

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.qtplaf.library.database.rdbms.sql.Statement
      • com.qtplaf.library.database.rdbms.sql.Insert

  • public class Insert
extends Statement
    A builder of INSERT statements. Insert can be of the following forms:
    1. INSERT INTO table SELECT view
    2. INSERT INTO table (fields...) VALUES (values...)
    3. INSERT INTO table a record.
    Author:
    Miquel Sas

      • setValues

        public void setValues(java.util.List<Value> values)
        Adds a list of values to build an insert statement of the form INSERT INTO table ( fields ) VALUES ( values ). This method can be called several times to create several insert operations. Obviously the values must correspond to the fields.
        Parameters:
        values - The list of values.

      • getRecord

        Returns:

      • setRecord

        public void setRecord(Record record)
        Adds the list of values to build an insert statement of the form INSERT INTO table ( fields ) VALUES ( values ) using the values given in the argument record. If the fields are not set and record has fields, the fields are taken from the record. Obviously the values in the record must correspond to the fields if already set.
        Parameters:
        record - The record to use to get the values.
